spoon.reflect.declaration.CtTypeParameter

Packages that use CtTypeParameter
Package
Description
spoon.reflect.declaration
This package contains the meta-model part that models the declarations (program's structures such as classes, fields, etc).
spoon.reflect.factory
This package defines all the sub-factories for the Spoon meta-model.
spoon.reflect.reference
This package defines the references to program elements for the meta-model.
spoon.reflect.visitor
This package defines visitor, scanner, and scanner-based query API for Java programs reified in the meta-model.
spoon.support
This package contains some default implementations for commonly used processing tasks.

  • Uses of CtTypeParameter in spoon.reflect.reference

    Methods in spoon.reflect.reference that return CtTypeParameter
    Modifier and Type
    Method
    Description
    CtTypeParameter
    CtTypeParameterReference.getDeclaration()
    Returns the CtTypeParameter, a CtTypeParameter, that declares the type parameter referenced or null if the reference is not in a context where such type parameter is declared.
    CtTypeParameter
    CtTypeReference.getTypeParameterDeclaration()
    If this type reference is used as a type argument (see CtActualTypeContainer.getActualTypeArguments()), returns the type parameter declaration in the target type, returns null otherwise.
